description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a permanent full time post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic individual to undertake the role of permanent, full time Band 4 Project Administrator in the Capital Planning Department based on the Morriston Hospital site in Swansea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide high level, comprehensive, professional and confidential business, administrative and on-site support to the Senior Management Team and wider Projects teams within Capital Planning department to assist with the planning and delivery of the directorate’s strategic objectives.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic individual with excellent communication and interpersonal skills as they will be liaising with a wide variety of personnel at all levels, both internal to the Health Board and from numerous external organisations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful postholder will need the ability to deal with complex information and to have excellent IT skills to be able to create, develop and maintain spreadsheets, databases and other electronic systems to capture financial information and maintain overall accurate departmental and project data. They will need to demonstrate they can develop and monitor financial and purchasing information and ensure accuracy of records.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who can manage their day to day workload with limited supervision, is able to act on their own initiative and who is able to cope with working to tight and multiple deadlines, in a constantly changing environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Hayley Richards-LewisCapital Support Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hayley.richards-lewis@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 704062&lt;/p&gt;
